{"word":"δυσκλεής","slug":"δυσκλεής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δυσκλεής</b></el> <el>(δυς-κλεής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κλέος'><el>κλέος</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <el>δυσκλέα</el> for <el>δυσκλεέα.</el>\n<p/><i>infamous, shameful</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b> <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-εῶς</el>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/>"}]}